properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 10:06PM MST until January 6 at 9:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HEAVY MOUNTAIN SNOW POSSIBLE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE MONDAY
EVENING...

* WHAT...Mainly blowing snow. Some light snow possible with
additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting
as high as 75 mph.

* WHERE...The northern Snowy Mountain Range, including Elk
Mountain and Arlington.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility to around one half
mile at times with snow drifts on area roadways.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM MST MONDAY
